<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="771" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d771">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/1697</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The British Ambassador on Special Mission</hi>
                                    (<persName corresp="#p_RERDI1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Reading</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d771fn1">Acknowledged without comment June
                                    6, 1918.</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 602</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-31">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 31, 1918</hi></date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received June 1.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I have received a
                                telegram from Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BAJ1">Balfour</persName>
                                informing me that he proposes shortly to make a statement in
                                Parliament in connection with the peace between the Central Powers
                                and Roumania, to the effect that the British Government will do all
                                they can, at the eventual peace conference, to obtain a revision of
                                the harsh terms imposed by the enemy upon Roumania. Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BAJ1">Balfour</persName> proposes to refer at the
                                same time to the protest made at Jassy by the ministers of the
                                Allied Powers, as well as to the reserves which were formulated by
                                the Allies in connection with the Danube convention.</p>
                            <p>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BAJ1">Balfour</persName> has requested me
                                to acquaint you in advance with his intention to make a statement on
                                the above lines.</p>
                            <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_RERDI1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reading</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>